# Commit authoring

Commits in this repo must be authored as **`Shayon Sanyal <shayons@amazon.com>`**
with **no `Co-authored-by: Cursor` trailer**.

Cursor's commit integration auto-injects a `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
trailer on every `git commit` (including `--amend`), so a normal commit cannot stay
clean. Create commits via git plumbing (`git commit-tree`), which bypasses that
injection.

## Make a commit (clean)

```bash
# 1. Stage as usual (do NOT stage .claude/settings.local.json)
git add <paths>

# 2. Build a tree from the index and commit it via plumbing
TREE=$(git write-tree)
PARENT=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
NEW=$(GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="Shayon Sanyal" GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="shayons@amazon.com" \
      GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Shayon Sanyal" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="shayons@amazon.com" \
      git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT" <<'EOF'
<commit subject>

<commit body>
EOF
)
git reset --soft "$NEW"   # move branch to the new commit, keep index/worktree
```

## Amend the latest commit message (clean)

```bash
TREE=$(git rev-parse HEAD^{tree})
PARENT=$(git rev-parse HEAD^)
ADATE=$(git show -s --format=%aI HEAD)
NEW=$(GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="Shayon Sanyal" GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="shayons@amazon.com" \
      GIT_AUTHOR_DATE="$ADATE" \
      GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Shayon Sanyal" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="shayons@amazon.com" \
      git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT" <<'EOF'
<new message>
EOF
)
git reset --soft "$NEW"
```

After creating/amending, verify: `git log -1 --format='%an <%ae>%n%B'` shows the
correct author and **no** `Co-authored-by` line. Force-pushing `main` (needed after
amending an already-pushed commit) requires explicit user approval; prefer
`--force-with-lease`.
